<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Scrabble Endgame Strategy</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Quiz · 3-letter words</p>

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 7 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8">The endgame is where club and tournament Scrabble is won and lost. Once the bag empties, the game transforms from probabilistic to deterministic — you can deduce exactly which tiles your opponent holds. Players who master endgame technique consistently gain 20-40 points over those who simply play their best-scoring word each turn.</p>

<div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8 p-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="text-center"><span class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">100</span><br><span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles in Standard Bag</span></div>
  <div class="text-center"><span class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7-12</span><br><span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Turns in Endgame</span></div>
  <div class="text-center"><span class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2x</span><br><span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Leftover Penalty</span></div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">When Does the Endgame Begin?</h2>

<p>Strictly, the endgame starts when the tile bag is empty. But skilled players begin preparing 3-5 turns earlier by tracking tiles and planning their exit strategy. The transition happens when you can count the remaining tiles and narrow down opponent holdings.</p>

<div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10 my-6">
  <p class="text-sm text-indigo-400 font-medium mb-1">💡 Key Insight</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">When 7 or fewer tiles remain in the bag, you should already know which tiles your opponent probably holds. Start adjusting your strategy based on what they are likely to play.</p>
</div>

<p>The game fundamentally changes at this point. During the mid-game, you play for your own rack quality. In the endgame, you play both sides of the board — maximising your score while minimising your opponent's options.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Tile Tracking Techniques</h2>

<p>Tile tracking means keeping a running tally of which tiles have been played. Since there are exactly 100 tiles with known quantities of each letter, subtracting played tiles reveals what remains unseen.</p>

<div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
<table class="w-full text-sm">
  <thead><tr class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800"><th class="p-2 text-left">Method</th><th class="p-2 text-left">Difficulty</th><th class="p-2 text-left">Accuracy</th><th class="p-2 text-left">Best For</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td class="p-2">Full tracking (all 27 tiles)</td><td class="p-2">Hard</td><td class="p-2">Perfect</td><td class="p-2">Tournament players</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-2">Power tile tracking (JQXZ + blanks)</td><td class="p-2">Medium</td><td class="p-2">High</td><td class="p-2">Club players</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="p-2">Vowel/consonant ratio</td><td class="p-2">Easy</td><td class="p-2">Moderate</td><td class="p-2">Beginners</td></tr>
    <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-2">S and blank tracking only</td><td class="p-2">Easy</td><td class="p-2">Good</td><td class="p-2">Casual competitive</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
</div>

<div class="space-y-3 my-6">
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Track the S tiles</span> — Four S tiles exist. Knowing if your opponent has one tells you whether they can pluralise for a big score.
  </div>
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Track the blanks</span> — Two blanks exist. An unplayed blank means your opponent could have a bingo waiting.
  </div>
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Count vowels remaining</span> — If the unseen pool is vowel-heavy, your opponent likely has a clunky rack with limited options.
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Q-Stick Scenarios & Prevention</h2>

<p>Getting stuck with the Q at game end (a "Q-stick") costs you 10 points in penalties and gifts your opponent 10 points — a 20-point swing. Avoiding this trap is one of the most critical endgame skills.</p>

<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-400 mb-2">Prevention Strategies</h3>
    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Play the Q early when U-spots are still open</li>
      <li>Keep QI available (requires I + open board spot)</li>
      <li>Hold a U as insurance if Q is unplayed</li>
      <li>Learn Q-without-U words: QI, QOPH, QADI, QANAT</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-2">When Opponent Has Q</h3>
    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Block the I-column plays (prevent QI)</li>
      <li>Close down open U-adjacent spots</li>
      <li>Play defensively to end the game quickly</li>
      <li>Force them to pass by blocking all Q-plays</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Playing for Spread</h2>

<p>In tournaments, your cumulative spread (total point differential across all games) breaks ties. This means the endgame is not just about winning — it is about winning by as much as possible, or losing by as little as possible.</p>

<div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10 my-6">
  <p class="text-sm text-indigo-400 font-medium mb-1">💡 Tournament Thinking</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">When winning comfortably, play your highest-scoring option even if it opens the board. When losing badly, play defensively to minimise the damage. Every point of spread matters across a 20+ game tournament.</p>
</div>

<p>The player who goes out first gains double the value of their opponent's remaining tiles. If your opponent holds QVWX (28 points), going out earns you 56 bonus points. This makes racing to empty your rack the dominant endgame strategy when ahead.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Closing Out Games</h2>

<p>The final 2-3 turns require precise calculation. You know exactly what your opponent holds, and you should simulate their best responses to each of your possible plays.</p>

<div class="space-y-3 my-6">
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Go-out plays</span> — If you can empty your rack this turn, calculate whether the bonus (2× opponent tiles) exceeds a higher-scoring play that leaves tiles.
  </div>
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Set-up plays</span> — Sometimes scoring less this turn to guarantee going out next turn is the optimal line.
  </div>
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Blocking plays</span> — If behind, block your opponent's best out-play even if it means scoring fewer points yourself.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10 my-6">
  <p class="text-sm text-indigo-400 font-medium mb-2">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
