<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Common Endgame Mistakes</h2>

<p>Even experienced players fall into these traps when the bag empties. Awareness alone eliminates most of these errors:</p>

<div class="space-y-3 my-6">
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Ignoring the out-play bonus:</span> Going out first gives you 2× your opponent's remaining tiles. A 25-point play that empties your rack often beats a 40-point play that leaves tiles behind.
  </div>
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Opening the board when ahead:</span> When you are winning, keep the board tight. Every open lane is an opportunity for your opponent to close the gap with a big play.
  </div>
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Not counting tiles:</span> With 14 or fewer tiles unseen, you should know every letter your opponent holds. If you do not, you are guessing — and guessing loses endgames.
  </div>
</div>

